\begin_layout Enumerate
Because a HomeoUnit is a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Newtonian
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 object: the input is a force (torque) that changes its velocity, not its
 position.
 A true Braitenberg vehicle would have to be 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Aristotelian,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 with input affecting its position, not its velocity.
 Newtonian physical laws approximate Aristotelian laws whenever friction
 forces are high.
 The only equivalent of friction forces in Homeo units is a negative self-connec
tion of the unit to itself.
 Such a connection will progressively decrease the value of the unit , hence
 the value of the motor unit it is connected to.
 It follows that a vehicle such implementing the diagram of figure 
