reference "fig:2-unit-setup-for-type-1"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

 will only have an Aristotelian behavior if the self-connection 
\begin_inset Formula $M\rightarrow M$
\end_inset

 is present.
 Otherwise put, a vehicle without such a selfc connection on its motor unit
 will always have a Newtonian behavior and will therefore nevr come to a
 stop once it gets going.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
There is another possible difference between the Homeo setup and Braitenberg's.
 The range of values of a Homeo unit is centered around 0, whereas the range
 of values of a Braitenberg's vehicle is always positive.
 The difference disappears if there are no self-connections, because the
 input value the input unit reads from the sensor can be assumed to be always
 positive (it is just scaled to the input unit's range, i.e.
 it is scaled to the range [
\begin_inset Formula $0,\ MaxDev$
\end_inset

]).
